description: More silly sexy fun from the creator of Spirit of Capitalism. To join the most popular club on campus, you’ve got to be totally hot, and willing to do anything to please the student body. Being a sex slave is wonderful!
name: Vol. 1
The Dark Queen's Wedding Part Two;

description:
Ultimatum has hit the planet hard and the Baxter Building was ground zero. Johnny is still missing. Dr. Storm is dead. And Reed has taken off to parts unknown. Sue's life hangs in the balance and rests in the hands of untested pilot Ben Grimm, a.k.a. The Thing, and Dr. Arthur Molekevic, now better known as the megalamonical Mole Man. "Journey to the Center of an Invisible Woman" begins!

This story is loosely based on the 1966 science-fiction film, Fantastic Voyage, where a submarine is shrunk and sent inside of a badly wounded scientist, in order to repair his wounds and save his life.
name: Journey to the Center of an Invisible Woman
Breaking The Curse, Part II; The Wax Museum;

description: It's the dawn of a new era for the Man of Steel and a great jumping-on point for new readers - and it's only 10 cents! With the debut of a new Superman creative team, the powerful new Superman villain Amok and the enigmatic Futuresmiths, this is an issue not to be missed - and at this price, you won't have to! And wait 'til you see the surprise on page 22!
name: Truth
The Dark Brethren Cometh, Part 3; Breaking The Curse;

description: Lonely Lex meets with her girlfriends at the local cafe where she describes one of the most horrible club experiences she has ever had in another installment of "Girl Talk." Vermilion, the ever increasingly bad goth poet plays a part in her misery, as well as some other never before featured characters. Max, too, makes an appearance in this issue, with love on his mind. Meanwhile Chrys is trying to reason with Sebastian as he goes a little mad in his attempt to separate reality from fantasy. And lastly, Damion confronts the wicked Isabella for the final time.
name: Sebastion’s Madness; Girl Talk; Wicked Dreams

description: The Earth's Sun is suffering a major, potentially cataclysmic, upheaval. Its temperature is rising at an impossible rate and enormous solar flares are erupting from the photosphere, sending fireballs directly to Earth. The Authority finds out that Winter, the former field commander of Stormwatch and an old friend of Hawksmoor's, is behind it.

Dedicated readers have long known that the medium of comics and graphic novels isn't all about caped superheroes. In fact, the combination of words and pictures can be the perfect vehicle for telling all kinds of stories. This collection of short stories illustrates, quite literally, the effectiveness of the medium for telling the most personal of stories -- the autobiography -- and does so by showcasing some of the first published autobiographical stories from living-legend artists, mainstream greats, and young "indie" up-and-comers.

According to Prometheus, Zeus has become a despot and must be stopped or at least halted by destroying a magical orb that is in Hades' care. Problem is, Hades is one of Zeus' most powerful allies. Atlas gathers Pandora and the Journeymen to stand by his side. But they need more power to stand a chance against Zeus and Hades. Who will they choose?

You’ve been asking for it…and now it’s here: THE CLONE SAGA!!! Marvel’s most controversial event of all time returns with a vengeance, presenting the Clone Saga as it was originally intended to be told! From the minds behind the crossover that changed comics forever and the artist that introduced Spider-Man to President Obama, it’s six issues of twists and turns that will shock fans old and new alike! Be here as Peter Parker’s worst nightmare begins again…now with an ending you have to see to believe!
name: The Clone Saga, Part One

description: When the Avengers return from the alternate reality world(they went there after they fought Onslaught),they are being attacked by Norse Mythology creatures.All available Avengers team-up with Thor to fight the Twilight Sword and the Norse Gems that were stolen from their homeland.This turned out to be a trap of the Celtic Sorceress Morgan Le Fay and her nephew,Mordred the Evil.
The Avengers time-travel to recruit a younger version of Iron Man. Alternate versions of various characters also turn up.

The island of Genosha has been a powderkeg since the X-Men overthrew its anti-mutant regime, and it's finally erupted into full-scale civil war! The president asks Professor X to mediate peace between human and mutant, but the situation is inflamed when Magneto's treacherous Acolyte Fabian Cortez makes a bid for power by kidnapping Luna, daughter of the Avengers' Quicksilver and Crystal - and Magneto's granddaughter! The X-Men and Avengers head for Genosha - but the situation spirals out of control when Magneto's right-hand man, Exodus, arrives looking to kill Cortez! Can even the X-Men and Avengers combined bring peace to a nation at war, defeat two madmen and save a child caught in the middle? Plus: the secret origin of Exodus and his twisted ties to the Avengers' Black Knight! Collecting AVENGERS (1963) #368-369, X-MEN (1991) #26, AVENGERS WEST COAST #101, UNCANNY X-MEN (1963) #307 and BLACK KNIGHT: EXODUS.
name: HC

description:
Enter the strange world of the Quiet Bird-Man: a world of mysterious corporations, foul-mouthed robots, drunken ghosts, amputee comedians, wealthy simian pornographers, and canine scientists; a world of disasters, murders, and masquerade balls. Jamie Tanner has been slowly weaving this dreamlike and darkly funny tale in anthologies and mini-comics for several years.

description: Separated into three parties, the gods, demi-gods and heroes travel to the underworld.

It's everything you ever wanted to know about the Earth's Mightiest Heroes in this new info-packed one-shot!  In the style and format of the ENCYCLOPEDIA DEADPOOLICA, this compilation gives both new readers and veteran fans the lowdown on Volume 3 of AVENGERS, covering AVENGERS #1-#22 as well as the 1998 and 1999 Annuals! Featuring behind-the-scenes info about the making of these classic stories! Plus: The definitive guide to the Avengers roster!
